or mode definitions in section 7 - the knowledge file describes both timeout and msgException cases as throwing exceptions, but I need to verify the exact exception types the source specifies for each mode. I'm checking the RST heading structure in the source document. The adornment characters define hierarchy based on their order of appearance, so I need to map out which character corresponds to which level—the equals signs for the title, then hyphens for the next level down. I'm working through the RST heading hierarchy more carefully now. The key insight is that heading levels are determined by the order in which adornment characters first appear, not by the characters themselves. So I need to trace through the document to see which underline character was encountered first as an underline-only adornment, then track how subsequent characters establish the hierarchy. I'm working through the RST heading structure more carefully now. Looking at the dashes and equals signs, I can see that \"障害系のテスト\" uses dashes that match the h2 level, but it's actually nested under \"テストデータの書き方\", making it h3. Then \"テスト結果検証\" also uses dashes at the h2 level. So the knowledge file's 8 sections map to a hierarchy where the main sections are split across multiple heading levels in the source document. I'm verifying that all class names and exceptions mentioned in the source are captured in the hints. Going through each section, I find that `MessageSendSyncTimeoutException` and `MessagingException` in s7 are already covered, and there don't appear to be any other class names that need to be added. The hints look comprehensive overall.\n\nLet me double-check s4 more carefully—the source references navigation links and an image that starts with \"![テストデータの\", but these are acceptable to omit since they're supplementary references rather than core content. After this review, I'm confident there are no critical omissions, no fabrications, and the section structure with sequential IDs s1